main event: Multiple UFO sightings were reported in Ukiah, California in the 1950s, including sightings of a silver, circular object, a yellow turret-shaped object, and a large object with blue-white lights moving at incredible speeds and changing positions.
interesting points: An object was observed to remain almost stationary in the sky for approximately 5 hours.
A yellow turret-shaped object was reported to hover approximately 4-5 feet above the ground before accelerating and disappearing to the south.
Several blue-white lights were observed changing positions on a large, fast-moving object with no sound or vapor trail.

Certified Weather Observer W. B. McKee reported observing a pulsating object at an altitude of approximately 25,000 feet, performing aerobatic-like maneuvers before accelerating into the distance and disappearing.
The State Highway Patrol officer described one of the UFO cases as 'one of the most outstanding' he had ever investigated.
sighted object: Various UFOs, including a silver, circular object, a yellow turret-shaped object, and a large object with blue-white lights
witnesses: Civilian observers, Mr. Walter Parrish, Ukiah, California, UKIAH CALIF. SHERIFF'S SGT. - MR. R. H. BROWN, Certified Weather Observer W. B. McKee
